<BlogPost
  title="Buy Once"
  description="No subscription. No recurring charge. You pay once, you own it."
  date="2026-04-03"
>

  <p>
    Pikos is free to download and use. If you buy it on the Mac App Store, you pay once and that's it. No monthly fee. No annual renewal. No "your trial has expired" pop-up after 14 days.
  </p>

  <h2>Why not a subscription</h2>

  <p>
    Subscriptions make sense when the company is running servers on your behalf — storing your files, syncing across devices, processing data. That costs real money every month, so charging every month is fair.
  </p>

  <p>
    Pikos doesn't run servers for you. Your data lives on your machine. The app runs on your hardware. The ongoing cost to us is close to zero per user, so charging you every month for it would be dishonest.
  </p>

  <h2>What you get</h2>

  <p>
    The free download is the full app. Everything works — notes, tasks, calendar, search, keyboard shortcuts, themes, export. Nothing is locked behind a paywall.
  </p>

  <p>
    The Mac App Store purchase is the same app, plus iCloud sync when it ships. Think of it as supporting development and getting sync as a bonus.
  </p>

  <h2>How this is sustainable</h2>

  <p>
    Honestly, it only works if enough people find the app valuable enough to buy it. There's no venture capital, no growth-at-all-costs pressure. Pikos is built by a small team with low overhead. We don't need millions of users to keep going — we need enough people who want a good tool and are willing to pay a fair price for it once.
  </p>

  <p>
    If that stops working, we'll figure something else out. But we won't retroactively add a subscription to an app you already paid for. That's a promise.
  </p>

</BlogPost>
